  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Childhood influenza coverage rates are far below rates for the other childhood vaccinations.
      Increasing influenza vaccine coverage rates is important not only for the health of the
      child, but for that of the child's household and community. Yet,influenza vaccine delivery
      rates at pediatric clinics are low, even when the vaccine is available. The proposed project
      will take advantage of existing health information technology to tailor, implement and
      evaluate influenza vaccine alerts in the electronic health record (EHR) for pediatric
      providers to help improve health care decision making.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
